# Next.js 16 Conventions (this repo)

This is Next 16.2.4 + Turbopack. Older patterns are traps.

## `src/proxy.ts`, NOT `src/middleware.ts`

`middleware.ts` is deprecated in Next 16. Use `src/proxy.ts` exporting a `proxy` function:

```ts
// src/proxy.ts
export async function proxy(request: NextRequest) { /* ... */ }
export const config = { matcher: ['/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico|.*\\.(?:svg|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|webp)$).*)'] };
```

## Never make auth-gating layouts async

`src/app/admin/layout.tsx` and `src/app/dashboard/layout.tsx` MUST be synchronous Server Components. No `async`, no `await`, no `redirect()`.

Async Server Component layouts that call `redirect()` during render crash Turbopack's dev tracer:
> `Failed to execute 'measure' on 'Performance': '​AdminLayout' cannot have a negative time stamp.`

All auth and role gating lives in `src/proxy.ts` instead.

### ❌ BAD
```tsx
export default async function AdminLayout({ children }) {
  const supabase = await createServerSupabaseClient();
  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
  if (!user) redirect('/auth/login');
  return <div>{children}</div>;
}
```

### ✅ GOOD
```tsx
export default function AdminLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <div>{children}</div>;
}
```
